{"title": "Movies and Hollywood Short Story Collection, Volume 1", "description": "Fiction about (or involving) motion pictures started appearing in the late nineteenth-century, when writers first became aware of early kinetoscope technologies. These stories grew more and more popular as the public became increasingly fascinated with the movies, the film industry, and the odd inhabitants of Hollywood. These stories reflect and often respond to the public's fascination with the movies; at the same time, they also reveal their fears and anxieties about the new medium. The first volume of this anthology collects 16 short stories and a monologue about motion picture technology and the film industry published between 1895 and 1922. (Summary by ChuckW)", "duration": 28011, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18", "name": " Various"}], "coverArt": "http://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt26/movies_hollywood1_1212.jpg", "copyright_year": "0", "genres": ["General Fiction", "Short Stories"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Chuck Williamson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Kinetoscope of Time", "readers": [7504], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/hollywoodshortstories001_1211_librivox/moviesandhollywood001_01_matthews_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1846}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Phantasmograph", "readers": [7138], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/hollywoodshortstories001_1211_librivox/moviesandhollywood001_02_pollock_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2266}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Vitagraphoscope", "readers": [7501], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/hollywoodshortstories001_1211_librivox/moviesandhollywood001_03_henry_64kb.mp3", "duration": 408}, {"section": 4, "title": "Mrs. Bathurst", "readers": [7500], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/hollywoodshortstories001_1211_librivox/moviesandhollywood001_04_kipling_6